d medal\", \"from\": 381, \"to\": 399}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tatjana Smith, the unequivocal Team SA golden girl of the Paris Olympics to date, could be closing in on another gold medal after claiming a comfortable place in the 200m breaststroke final.\", \"from\": 404, \"to\": 594, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Tatjana Smith\", \"from\": 404, \"to\": 417}, {\"ngram\": \"the unequivocal Team SA golden girl\", \"from\": 419, \"to\": 454}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 458, \"to\": 476}, {\"ngram\": \"date\", \"from\": 480, \"to\": 484}, {\"ngram\": \"another gold medal\", \"from\": 509, \"to\": 527}, {\"ngram\": \"a comfortable place\", \"from\": 543, \"to\": 562}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Smith was widely expected to win her semi-final, but touched the wall in 2:19:94, just behind surprise winner Kate Douglass.\", \"from\": 596, \"to\": 720, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 706, \"end\": 719, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kate Douglass\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Smith\", \"from\": 596, \"to\": 601}, {\"ngram\": \"the wall\", \"from\": 657, \"to\": 665}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nevertheless, she has comfortably progressed to the the final, with the top 8 set to now race for medal places onThursday, 1 Augustjust after 21:00 (SA time), with Smith joined byKaylene Corbettafter she impressively finished second in the first semi-final.\", \"from\": 722, \"to\": 979, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the top 8 set\", \"from\": 790, \"to\": 803}, {\"ngram\": \"medal places\", \"from\": 820, \"to\": 832}, {\"ngram\": \"Smith\", \"from\": 886, \"to\": 891}, {\"ngram\": \"byKaylene Corbettafter\", \"from\": 899, \"to\": 921}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Earlier on Wednesday, Smith, swim